gram\": \"local virus transmission\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS PublishedMar 24, 2024, 10:05 AM UpdatedMar 24, 2024, 05:39 PM PARIS-France is scrambling to make sure that virus-carrying tiger mosquitoes, a growing menace in Europe, do not spoil the Paris Olympics for athletes and fans, with millions of visitors due in the French capital for the Summer Games.\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9549408743871035, \"rank\": 0.045965954223067984, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 329}, {\"ngram\": \"10:05 AM\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"UpdatedMar\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"PARIS-France\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"virus-carrying tiger mosquitoes\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 477}, {\"ngram\": \"a growing menace\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 505}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 560}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Asian tiger mosquito has made its home in much of northern Europe, including France, over the past two decades, spreading diseases such as dengue, chikungunya and zika.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}, {\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asian tiger mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aedes_albopictus\"}, {\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 0.9999999879460121, \"rank\": 1.2053825978964578e-08, \"text\": \"mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its home\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"northern Europe\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 709}, {\"ngram\": \"the past two decades\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"diseases\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"dengue\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"chikungunya\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"zika\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate change is said to be behind its easy adaptation to colder climes, with the authorities recently declaring Normandy in the north-west, the last remaining mosquito-free region in all of France, infestedjust like the rest of the country.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy_landings\", \"score\": 0.6237989999318042, \"rank\": 0.5975675868399872, \"text\": \"Normandy\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy_landings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy_landings\"}, {\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Climate change\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 828}, {\"ngram\": \"its easy adaptation\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 869}, {\"ngram\": \"climes\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"the authorities\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 908}, {\"ngram\": \"the north-west\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 954}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The authorities have tried in vain to get rid of the insects, including by fumigating parts of Paris, a technique regularly used in tropical cities.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.238718104260799e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The authorities\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"vain\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"the insects\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1118}, {\"ngram\": \"fumigating parts\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"a technique\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"tropical cities\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But with the start of the Paris Games only four months away, they are on the clock, with experts warning that a tiger mosquito bite could destroy an athlete's chance of making it to the starting line.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"the clock\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"experts\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"a tiger\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"mosquito bite\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's chance\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"the starting line\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When you are sick with dengue, you will not be jumping over any hurdles,\\\" said entomologist Didier Fontenille, an expert on vector-borne diseases.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"score\": 0.9999999849433153, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fontenille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dengue\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"any hurdles\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"entomologist\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"an expert\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"vector-borne diseases\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The host cities and especially the Olympic Village must be kept mosquito-free,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1595, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.926290404307736e-12, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The host cities\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Health authorities have promised \\\"increased surveillance\\\" of the mosquito threat, which has been notoriously difficult to eliminate.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1715, \"end\": 1723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 0.9999999879460121, \"rank\": 1.2053825978964578e-08, \"text\": \"mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Health authorities\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"increased surveillance\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France reported 45 dengue cases in 2023, attributed to local virus transmission.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999722862596614, \"rank\": 2.4694244440384537e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"45 dengue cases\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"local virus transmission\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tiger mosquitoes are happiest in cities, where an abundant presence of stagnant water creates ideal conditions for laying their eggs.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1999, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tiger mosquitoes\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1882}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1905}, {\"ngram\": \"an abundant presence\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1933}, {\"ngram\": \"stagnant water\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1951}, {\"ngram\": \"ideal conditions\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"their eggs\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 1998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Fontenille said dealing with stagnant water would \\\"take care of 80 per cent of the problem\\\" if there was a \\\"citizens' mobilisation\\\" to clean up even smallest amounts of water left in flower bowls or saucers.\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2004, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"score\": 0.9999999849433153, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fontenille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontenille\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"stagnant water\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2047}, {\"ngram\": \"care\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"80 per cent\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2094}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"citizens' mobilisation\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"even smallest amounts\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2178}, {\"ngram\": \"flower bowls\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"saucers\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2210}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the rest, he said, repellents, mosquito nets and organic insecticides used on mosquito larvae could be effective.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"repellents\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2246}, {\"ngram\": \"mosquito nets\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"organic insecticides\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2286}, {\"ngram\": \"mosquito larvae\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mosquito traps also show promise, using simulated human body odours to attract, and then kill, the mosquitoes.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.899219894359951e-46, \"text\": \"Mosquito\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mosquito\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"promise\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2364}, {\"ngram\": \"simulated human body odours\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"the mosquitoes\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2441}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A variation consists of fooling the insects into laying their eggs in the trap, where they are destroyed.\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2548, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A variation\", \"from\": 2443, \"to\": 2454}, {\"ngram\": \"the insects\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"their eggs\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2509}, {\"ngram\": \"the trap\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biogents, a specialist firm, said it won a public bid to protect the Marseille Marina, the site of sailing competitions, with its plan to install 15 traps.\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biogents\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"a specialist firm\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"a public bid\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"the Marseille Marina\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2635}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2645}, {\"ngram\": \"sailing competitions\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2669}, {\"ngram\": \"its plan\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"15 traps\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2704}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Co-manager Hugo Plan said they would be set up in April, spread over 1ha \\\"in greenery and in shaded, humid areas\\\".\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Co-manager Hugo Plan\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2762}, {\"ngram\": \"greenery\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2792}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the Games, staff will regularly check the